<li id="cite_note-paoli33-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-paoli33_31-0" title="">^</a></b> The sect made <i>"affiliates every day of the brightest young people coming from the rural class, of the guardians of the fields in the Palermitan countryside, and of the large number of smugglers; a sect which gives and receives protection to and from certain men who make a living on traffic and internal commerce. It is a sect with little or no fear of public bodies, because its members believe that they can easily elude this."</i> See: Paoli, <i>Mafia Brotherhoods</i>, p. 33 (Colonna seemed to have known what he was talking about, there was widespread suspicion that he was the protector of some important Mafiosi in Palermo)</li>
